DENGUE - ARGENTINA, BRAZIL, PARAGUAY: ALERT
**********************************************
A ProMED-mail message
<http://www.promedmail.org>
Date: 13 Feb 2000
From: Dr. Oscar P. Larghi <oplarghi@drwebsa.com.ar>
Source: La Nacion, Argentina 13 Feb 2000 [in Spanish]
[Translated & edited by Mod.JW]

National health authorities in Argentina have declared a dengue alert after
finding cases in travelers returning from Brazil & Ciudad del Este,
Paraguay. 5 cases were detected in Buenos Aires Province, in Lanas,
Berazategui & Ituzaingo (to the south & west of Greater Buenos Aires) & 2
in Corrientes (NE of the country). 5000 cases have been reported in Paraguay.
The Ministry of Health confirms the presence of _Aedes aegypti_, the
mosquito vector of dengue, in various zones in the north of the country, &
also in the city of Buenos Aires.
--
Dr. Oscar P. Larghi
Fray Lamas 248
1706 Haedo, BA, ARGENTINA
